{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP applies: this is extraction quality, not just wiring. A mock extractor could always return expected keys and miss real semantic misses/omissions. No multi-step agent chain is required beyond one reviewer call.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a curated set of real contract snippets with gold annotations for parties/dates/obligations/penalties, and assert recall/precision thresholds per term type. Include edge phrasing and nested clauses to catch real model misses.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk assessor flags language that would be problematic under the configured risk policy, even when the problematic phrasing is indirect or euphemistic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on nuanced semantic interpretation (indirect/euphemistic risk language), which mocks or deterministic stubs would hide. This is model judgment quality at a single reviewer boundary.","test_description":"Invoke the real risk-assessor model with real policy config on a benchmark set containing direct and euphemistic risky phrasing, then verify expected high-risk flags (and acceptable false-negative ceiling). Repeat runs to detect instability around borderline language.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.89,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The compliance checker correctly determines whether the contract meets all applicable regulatory requirements for the configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Even with jurisdiction config, the key failure boundary is model interpretation of legal text against requirements. Pure mocks can hide misclassification. This is one agentic decision step, not a multi-agent workflow by itself.","test_description":"Call the real compliance-checker model using real jurisdiction configs on contracts with expert-labeled compliant/non-compliant outcomes and requirement-level rationales; assert decision accuracy and requirement coverage thresholds per jurisdiction.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (e.g., extractor says \"standard\" but risk assessor says \"high risk\"), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS applies at module wiring/schema boundary: conflict preservation and attribution can fail due to field mapping, ID alignment, or serialization between reviewer outputs and merge logic. No real LLM call is required to catch this class of failure.","test_description":"Feed the merge component realistic reviewer output payloads (including conflicting assessments on same clause ID, partial metadata, and ordering variance) through the actual parser/normalizer + merger modules, then assert both assessments are present with correct reviewer attribution and no overwrite.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP applies: three real AI reviewer calls plus aggregation/merge. Failures can emerge from parallel dispatch, asynchronous collection, partial retries, and final merge under real agentic outputs. Lower-level mocks can hide dropped findings and timing issues.","test_description":"Execute an end-to-end run on real contract documents using all three real reviewer services in parallel, then validate the final unified report contains every reviewer finding (with provenance) and expected conflict handling. Include assertions for no dropped reviewer sections under concurrent execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.23,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
